TITLE: JD Vance hits multiple networks in Sunday morning media flurry as Tim Walz lays low
SUMMARY: JD Vance gave multiple interviews with major networks on Sunday, but his counterpart, Tim Walz, did not speak to the media.

TITLE: Harris slammed as 'CopyCatKamala' for following Trump's lead on exempting taxes on tips
SUMMARY: Critics on social media are slamming Vice President Kamala Harris as a "copy cat" after she vowed to not tax service industry tips, following former President Trump's lead.

TITLE: Ex-North Dakota politician admits to traveling to Czech Republic for sex with minor
SUMMARY: Former North Dakota lawmaker Ray Holmberg has pleaded guilty to traveling to Europe with the intent to pay for sex with a minor during multiple trips to the Czech Republic.

TITLE: 2024 showdown: New polls this weekend in three key battlegrounds in Harris-Trump White House race
SUMMARY: New polling in three battleground states that may determine the 2024 White House election show Vice President Harris ahead of former President Trump.

TITLE: Secret Service apologizes after breaking into Massachusetts salon to use bathroom before Harris fundraiser
SUMMARY: Secret Service are facing scrutiny over their treatment of a local salon in Massachusetts ahead of a fundraiser for Vice President Kamala Harris.

TITLE: With 26 days until voting starts, 'election season' kicks off sooner than you think
SUMMARY: Early voting begins as soon as Sept. 6 for Americans who are eligible, and if the last two election cycles are any indication, many citizens will have already voted.

TITLE: Gov. Abbott issues executive order requiring Texas hospitals to gather data on immigration statuses
SUMMARY: Texas Gov. Greg Abbott issued an executive order requiring public hospitals in the Lone Star State to collect information on patients' immigration statuses.

TITLE: Veteran Bob McDermott wins 6-way GOP primary to face Mazie Hirono for Senate in deep-blue Hawaii
SUMMARY: Six Republican hopefuls faced off in the primary to challenge Democratic Sen. Mazie Hirono in November.

TITLE: Retired cops in Congress shred Dem's push for mandated police 'cultural diversity' training
SUMMARY: House Republican law enforcement veterans are responding to a Democratic push to add sensitivity training to police recruits' curriculum.

TITLE: Balance of power: Trump campaign slams Sen Tester as 'radically out of touch' after abortion ad rollout
SUMMARY: Jon Tester rolled out several ads on abortion, claiming his Republican opponent would let abortion be banned without exceptions. The Trump campaign accused Tester of not believing in any limitations on the procedure.

TITLE: Rep. Ed Case wins Dem primary, setting up for 6th full term in deep blue Hawaii
SUMMARY: Representative Ed Case won his primary in Hawaii's 1st Congressional District on Saturday and is the favorite to win the seat in November.

TITLE: Mazie Hirono wins Hawaii Senate primary, setting Dems up for much-needed November win
SUMMARY: Sen. Mazie Hirono easily won her second Senate re-election campaign in Hawaii and is the favorite to win a third term in November.

TITLE: Trump accuses Harris of 'stealing' his no tax on tips promise after her campus rally in Las Vegas
SUMMARY: Former President Trump accused Vice President Kamala Harris for 'stealing' his no tax on tips policy after she parroted the same policy at a rally in Las Vegas.

TITLE: Harris voters defend Democratic presidential nominee on Israel-Hamas conflict: ‘She’s married to a Jewish guy’
SUMMARY: Vice President Kamala Harris' stance on Israel and Gaza has been at the fore in recent weeks. Fox News Digital questioned rallygoers in Arizona and Nevada about her policy platform.

TITLE: Newsom cleans up homeless California encampments after he allocated billions of dollars while crisis grew
SUMMARY: Newsom cleaned up trash from homeless encampments in Los Angeles and warned municipalities they’ll lose state funding if they don’t do more to clear them across the state.

TITLE: Las Vegas rideshare drivers laud Trump’s ‘awesome’ no-tax-on-tips plan as Harris holds rally across town
SUMMARY: Rideshare drivers across Las Vegas voiced support for former President Trump's stated plan to end taxation of gratuities to lessen inflation's blow on service industry workers.

TITLE: Trump campaign says internal communications were hacked, including Vance 'dossier,' by foreign sources
SUMMARY: Former President Trump's campaign said on Saturday that some of its internal communications had been hacked, possibly by Iran, which was also linked to a foiled assassination plot.

TITLE: Minnesota teacher pension fund under Walz accused of 'cooking the books' with unrealistic gains: report
SUMMARY: Under Gov. Walz, Minnesota’s Teachers Retirement Association is accused by a pension investigator of hiding fees and reporting implausibly high returns, termed a "Madoff miracle."

TITLE: Herbert Hoover’s humanitarian work is long remembered, but his presidency was tainted by the Great Depression
SUMMARY: Herbert Hoover is remembered at "the great humanitarian." Hoover took office in 1929, just months before the Great Depressions began in the United States.

TITLE: GOP states sue to stop Biden admin extending Obamacare to illegal immigrants
SUMMARY: Fifteen Republican-led states are suing the Biden administration over a rule that would allow some illegal immigrants to gain access to healthcare under Obamacare.

TITLE: RFK Jr. claims to have enough signatures to appear on ballot in all 50 states
SUMMARY: Independent presidential candidate Robert F. Kennedy told Fox News's Neil Cavuto on Friday that he has enough signatures to appear on the ballot in all 50 states.

TITLE: Minnesota Dem lawmaker defends Walz against 'radical' label from GOP: 'Couldn't disagree more'
SUMMARY: Democratic Minnesota State Sen. Nick Frentz spoke with Fox News Digital about Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz, shutting down criticism of the governor amid his vice presidential campaign.

TITLE: VP snub Gov. Josh Shapiro touts $1.1 billion increase in his state’s public school funding
SUMMARY: Pennsylvania Gov. Josh Shapiro highlighted the record $1.1 billion in additional public education funding in the commonwealth's next budget during a celebratory signing.

TITLE: Harris' VP pick Walz a big win for teachers' unions that pushed schools to stay shuttered for over a year
SUMMARY: Critics are warning that Democratic presidential nominee Kamala Harris’ selection of Minnesota Gov. Tim Walz as her vice president should raise alarm bells for parents and children in the public education system.

TITLE: A top Senate Republican crisscrosses campaign trail in 'make-or-break moment' to win back majority
SUMMARY: Senate Republican Whip John Thune of South Dakota, who is running to succeed longtime GOP leader Mitch McConnell, is crisscrossing the campaign trail to help win back the chamber's majority.
